Public transport (MHD) in Prague will introduce the hole in their ticket system on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be included in the history of Pražský Dovravní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will enter the metro, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible to nearly one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day or 90-day fee (this one will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both have it recorded on their chip card in the information points and offices of the Dovravní pondnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Mostek, Nádraži Holesovice, Andel, Roztyly, Latvian, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy online coupons on the web pages of the Dovravní podnik: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people enjoyed the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can definitively forget the holes in the metro stations, where they had to wait for patience in long queues to get paper tickets.
In fact, they will purchase their coupon online and will be registered on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is a gate with trained staff available to passengers, who will help interested people with the purchase of the internet and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said the spokesman of the Martin Opatrný project.
Alongside libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the lobby of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and the passengers may have already noticed them in the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be twenty-four," said Opatrný.
An auto will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just insert the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
